<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-560-431  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 560 431.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 30 1990 v4 n37 p15(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gold Disk promises easy animation. (Animation Works multimediasoftware) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Said, Carolyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gold Disk Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Animation Works (Computer graphics software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionComputer GraphicsMultimedia SoftwareAnimationMotion Pictures.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Carolyn SaidandM;Toronto -- Arguing that movie making should be as easy as drawing a line,Gold Disk Inc. introduced Animation Works, a path-based animation softwarepackage, at last week's Macworld Expo here.andM;Designed to attract a broader audience, including educators, small-businessowners and graphic designers, to Mac-based animation, the program will shipin November for $199.95.andP;  It runs on all Mac models, including the newlost-cost Macs, the company said.andM;Animation Works has three modules:andM;andgt;Background Editor, an eight-bit color paint program for creating and editingbackgrounds.andP;  Along with import capabilities and an array of drawing tools,brush shapes and special effects, it offers custom, radial and graduatedfills and extensive text support.andM;andgt;Cel Editor, used to create and edit &quot;actors.&quot; In addition to paint andimport capabilities, the Cel Editor has special tools for registration and anOnion Skin feature so users can see up to seven cels (representations of animage at different stages) simultaneously to ensure smooth animation.andP;  Alibrary of actors will be included.andM;andgt;Movie Editor, which is used to combine actors and backgrounds to formmovies.andP;  Users draw lines to indicate paths (the motion of actors throughframes), which can be linear, elliptical, freehand or polygonal.andP;  Otherspecial path types include gravitationally correct movement, preciselyregistered motion, and hierarchical paths in which the motion of one path islinked to another.andM;Users can view a production as a storyboard showing all or user-specifiedkeyframes.andP;  Storyboards can be annotated with comments and printed.andM;Special effects include wipes, animated mattes, scrolling backgrounds, colorcycling, variable playback speeds and pauses.andP;  Sounds in snd or MacRecorderformats can be attached to any frame.andM;A runtime player module and HyperCard external commands (XCMDs) for playinganimations from stacks will be included.andM;Gold Disk, which said it is the largest worldwide publisher of software forthe Commodore Amiga, plans to extend its Mac presence with a $495 higher-endanimation package, due in the first quarter of 1991, that will support 24-bitcolor, point-and-click interactivity, and full anti-aliasing.andM;Gold Disk Inc. is located at 5155 Spectrum Way, Unit 5, Mississauga, Ontario,Canada L4W 5A1; (416) 602-4000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>